  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PII redaction transforms identified sensitive spans into safer representations before text is stored, logged, sent to an LLM, or returned to users. The right redaction strategy depends on whether the downstream system needs to recover the original value, maintain referential consistency across records, or simply ensure the PII cannot be read."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Five PII redaction strategies compared: type replacement, masking, pseudonymization, tokenization, generalization, synthetic replacement"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategy 1: Type Replacement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Replace each PII span with a bracketed type label. Simple, fast, and unambiguous. The output preserves sentence structure while making the PII category visible to downstream readers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass PIISpan:\n    entity_type: str\n    text: str\n    start: int\n    end: int\n\ndef type_replace(text: str, spans: list[PIISpan]) -> str:\n    result = list(text)\n    for span in sorted(spans, key=lambda s: s.start, reverse=True):\n        replacement = f'[{span.entity_type}]'\n        result[span.start:span.end] = list(replacement)\n    return ''.join(result)\n\n# Example:\n# spans = [PIISpan('PERSON', 'John Smith', 0, 10),\n#          PIISpan('EMAIL', 'john@acme.com', 18, 31)]\n# type_replace('John Smith sent john@acme.com a note.', spans)\n# -> '[PERSON] sent [EMAIL] a note.'"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use type replacement when downstream consumers need to know what "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "kind",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " of PII was present (for audit logs, compliance reports) but not the actual values."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategy 2: Pseudonymization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Replace each unique PII value with a consistent surrogate label. If the same person appears multiple times, they always map to the same label. This preserves referential consistency (useful for analytics) while removing the actual identifiers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from collections import defaultdict\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nclass Pseudonymizer:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._map: dict[tuple[str, str], str] = {}\n        self._counts: dict[str, int] = defaultdict(int)\n\n    def pseudonym(self, entity_type: str, value: str) -> str:\n        key = (entity_type, value)\n        if key not in self._map:\n            self._counts[entity_type] += 1\n            self._map[key] = f'{entity_type}_{self._counts[entity_type]}'\n        return self._map[key]\n\n    def redact(self, text: str, spans: list[PIISpan]) -> str:\n        result = list(text)\n        for span in sorted(spans, key=lambda s: s.start, reverse=True):\n            replacement = self.pseudonym(span.entity_type, span.text)\n            result[span.start:span.end] = list(replacement)\n        return ''.join(result)\n\n    def mapping(self) -> dict:\n        return {v: k[1] for k, v in self._map.items()}\n\n# Example across multiple records:\n# p = Pseudonymizer()\n# p.redact('John Smith signed.', [PIISpan('PERSON','John Smith',0,10)])\n# -> 'PERSON_1 signed.'\n# p.redact('John Smith called.', [PIISpan('PERSON','John Smith',0,10)])\n# -> 'PERSON_1 called.'  (same pseudonym \u2014 consistency preserved)\n# p.redact('Jane Doe replied.', [PIISpan('PERSON','Jane Doe',0,8)])\n# -> 'PERSON_2 replied.'  (different person, different pseudonym)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Pseudonymization is reversible using the mapping table. The mapping table is itself sensitive data \u2014 store it with the same security controls as the original PII. GDPR treats pseudonymized data as personal data if the mapping is retained."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategy 3: Tokenization with a Vault"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tokenization replaces PII values with opaque random tokens stored in a secure token vault. Unlike pseudonymization, the token has no structural relationship to the original value \u2014 an attacker who sees "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TKN_8a2f",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " learns nothing about the original:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import secrets\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nclass TokenVault:\n    def __init__(self, vault_path: Optional[str] = None):\n        self._vault: dict[str, str] = {}  # token -> original value\n        self._reverse: dict[str, str] = {}  # value -> token\n        self._path = vault_path\n        if vault_path and Path(vault_path).exists():\n            with open(vault_path) as f:\n                data = json.load(f)\n                self._vault = data['vault']\n                self._reverse = data['reverse']\n\n    def tokenize(self, value: str) -> str:\n        if value in self._reverse:\n            return self._reverse[value]\n        token = 'TKN_' + secrets.token_hex(4).upper()\n        self._vault[token] = value\n        self._reverse[value] = token\n        return token\n\n    def detokenize(self, token: str) -> Optional[str]:\n        return self._vault.get(token)\n\n    def redact(self, text: str, spans: list[PIISpan]) -> str:\n        result = list(text)\n        for span in sorted(spans, key=lambda s: s.start, reverse=True):\n            token = self.tokenize(span.text)\n            result[span.start:span.end] = list(token)\n        return ''.join(result)\n\n    def save(self) -> None:\n        if self._path:\n            with open(self._path, 'w') as f:\n                json.dump({'vault': self._vault, 'reverse': self._reverse}, f)\n\n# Usage:\n# vault = TokenVault('/secure/path/vault.json')\n# redacted = vault.redact(text, spans)\n# vault.save()\n# # Later: restore original\n# original = vault.detokenize('TKN_8A2F')"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategy 4: Generalization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Replace specific PII with broader, less-identifying descriptions. Useful when the text must remain readable and approximately meaningful, but exact values are unnecessary:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re\n\ndef generalize_span(span: PIISpan) -> str:\n    rules = {\n        'EMAIL':    '[an email address]',\n        'PHONE_US': '[a US phone number]',\n        'PERSON':   '[a person]',\n        'SSN':      '[a social security number]',\n        'CC_VISA':  '[a payment card number]',\n        'GPE':      '[a location]',\n        'DATE':     lambda span: generalize_date(span.text),\n        'API_KEY':  '[an API credential]',\n    }\n    rule = rules.get(span.entity_type, f'[{span.entity_type.lower()}]')\n    return rule(span) if callable(rule) else rule\n\ndef generalize_date(date_str: str) -> str:\n    # Generalize precise dates to year or month-year\n    year_match = re.search(r'\\b(19|20)\\d{2}\\b', date_str)\n    if year_match:\n        return f'[a date in {year_match.group()}]'\n    return '[a date]'\n\ndef generalize(text: str, spans: list[PIISpan]) -> str:\n    result = list(text)\n    for span in sorted(spans, key=lambda s: s.start, reverse=True):\n        replacement = generalize_span(span)\n        result[span.start:span.end] = list(replacement)\n    return ''.join(result)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Strategy 5: Synthetic Replacement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Replace PII with realistic but entirely fabricated values of the same type. The result reads naturally and preserves the document's structure, making it suitable for testing, demos, and sharing sanitized examples:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import random\nimport string\n\n# Simple synthetic generators (production: use Faker library)\n\nFIRST_NAMES = ['Alice', 'Bob', 'Carol', 'David', 'Eva', 'Frank']\nLAST_NAMES  = ['Johnson', 'Williams', 'Brown', 'Davis', 'Miller']\nDOMAINS     = ['example.com', 'example.org', 'example.net']\n\ndef synthetic_person() -> str:\n    return f'{random.choice(FIRST_NAMES)} {random.choice(LAST_NAMES)}'\n\ndef synthetic_email(name: Optional[str] = None) -> str:\n    user = name.lower().replace(' ', '.') if name else 'user'\n    return f'{user}@{random.choice(DOMAINS)}'\n\ndef synthetic_phone() -> str:\n    return f'555-{random.randint(100,999)}-{random.randint(1000,9999)}'\n\ndef synthetic_replace(text: str, spans: list[PIISpan]) -> str:\n    result = list(text)\n    person_name = None\n    for span in sorted(spans, key=lambda s: s.start, reverse=True):\n        if span.entity_type == 'PERSON':\n            person_name = synthetic_person()\n            replacement = person_name\n        elif span.entity_type == 'EMAIL':\n            replacement = synthetic_email(person_name)\n        elif span.entity_type in ('PHONE_US', 'PHONE'):\n            replacement = synthetic_phone()\n        else:\n            replacement = f'[SYNTHETIC_{span.entity_type}]'\n        result[span.start:span.end] = list(replacement)\n    return ''.join(result)\n\n# Production: use the Faker library for locale-aware synthetic data\n# from faker import Faker\n# fake = Faker()\n# fake.name(), fake.email(), fake.phone_number(), fake.address()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-Aware Redaction: Prompting for Redacted Output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When an LLM generates a response that may contain PII (e.g., it read PII from a retrieved document), you can instruct it to self-redact during generation. This is complementary to post-generation scanning, not a replacement:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nREDACT_SYSTEM = '''You are a helpful assistant.\nIMPORTANT: You must NEVER include in your response:\n- Full names of real people\n- Email addresses\n- Phone numbers\n- Social Security Numbers or national ID numbers\n- Home or physical addresses\n- Financial account numbers\n- API keys, passwords, or credentials\n\nIf you must refer to a person, use only their role (e.g., 'the customer', 'the employee').\nIf asked to repeat or quote text that contains PII, redact it with [REDACTED] first.'''\n\ndef redacted_completion(user_message: str,\n                        context: str = '') -> str:\n    messages = []\n    if context:\n        messages.append({\n            'role': 'user',\n            'content': f'Context (may contain PII \u2014 redact before quoting):\\n{context}',\n        })\n        messages.append({'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Understood. I will redact PII.'})\n    messages.append({'role': 'user', 'content': user_message})\n\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model='claude-sonnet-4-6',\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=REDACT_SYSTEM,\n        messages=messages,\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "LLM self-redaction is imperfect \u2014 models sometimes reproduce PII despite instructions to the contrary. Always layer post-generation scanning on top of self-redaction prompting. Neither alone is sufficient."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
